dismissalText.commentary: Prabhsimran Singh b Mukesh Kumar 103 (65b 10x4 6x6 87m) SR: 158.46

dismissalComment.html: Mukesh gets Prabhsimran! Low full toss angled into leg stump. Prabhsimran tries to be too funky and looks for the reverse ramp. Does not have the room to work with and in the end, the ball pings off his pads into the stumps. Take nothing away from this sensational innings, though!

dismissalText.commentary: Shikhar Dhawan c Rossouw b Sharma 7 (5b 0x4 1x6 9m) SR: 140

dismissalComment.html: holes out to deep square leg, oh my! Full and angled into the pads. On most days, Dhawan would have smashed that into the stands. Today, though, he can only hit it straight down Rossouw's throat at deep square leg. Not the greatest delivery Ishant has ever bowled but both he and DC will not mind this wicket one bit!

dismissalText.commentary: Liam Livingstone b Sharma 4 (5b 1x4 0x6 15m) SR: 80

dismissalComment.html: and he knocks Livingstone over! Length delivery slanted into middle and off stump. Livingstone comes down the track and looks to smash it into next week. Loses his shape completely, though, and gets nowhere close to the ball as it cannons into middle and off stump! Ishant waves Livingstone goodbye and PBKS are two down in the powerplay!

dismissalText.commentary: Jitesh Sharma b Patel 5 (5b 1x4 0x6 8m) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: Jitesh bites the dust too! Slowed up nicely on a length on off stump. Jitesh backs away and looks to go inside out. He is nowhere close to the pitch of the ball, though, and has a swish at it. The ball breezes past the bat and then thuds into the top of off stump!

images.caption: Axar Patel celebrates Jitesh Sharma's wicket
images.longCaption: Axar Patel celebrates Jitesh Sharma's wicket, Delhi Capitals vs Punjab Kings, IPL 2023, Delhi, May 13, 2023

dismissalText.long: c Aman Hakim Khan b Dubey
dismissalText.commentary: Sam Curran c Aman Hakim Khan b Dubey 20 (24b 1x4 0x6 39m) SR: 83.33

dismissalComment.html: Curran perishes! Back of a length delivery on middle and leg stump that spins back into Curran and cramps him for room. He tries to advance and clear long on but just does not have enough room to work with. Splices it towards long on, where Aman does the rest!

dismissalText.commentary: Harpreet Brar c Marsh b Kuldeep Yadav 2 (5b 0x4 0x6 9m) SR: 40

dismissalComment.html: soft dismissal! Length delivery on middle and off stump. Brar is caught on the crease and then ends up offering the simplest of catches to extra cover. Not sure what Brar was trying there but either way, this PBKS experiment has fallen flat on its face!

dismissalText.commentary: M Shahrukh Khan run out (†Salt/Ahmed) 2 (4b 0x4 0x6 22m) SR: 50

dismissalComment.html: swing and a miss again! And Shahrukh is also run out at the bowler's end! Slower delivery on a back of a length outside off stump. Shahrukh swings like a rusty gate and does not make contact. Raza calls him through for a bye but Shahrukh is nowhere in the frame as Salt relays it to Khaleel, who takes off the bails at the bowler's end!

dismissalText.commentary: Sikandar Raza not out 11 (7b 0x4 1x6 11m) SR: 157.14

dismissalComment.html: huge appeal, not given! Full delivery fired into leg stump. The ball goes past the bat and hits Warner on the pads. That might have pitched outside leg, though, and that is why the umpire has given it not out. PBKS want to check upstairs! No bat involved, according to UltraEdge and the ball has pitched in line. It goes on to hit leg stump too, and Warner has to walk back!

images.longCaption: A dejected David Warner walks off after his 27-ball 54, Delhi Capitals vs Punjab Kings, IPL 2023, Delhi, May 13, 2023

images.longCaption: Harpreet Brar celebrates after a successful review for lbw, Delhi Capitals vs Punjab Kings, IPL 2023, Delhi, May 13, 2023

dismissalText.commentary: Phil Salt b Harpreet Brar 21 (17b 3x4 0x6 31m) SR: 123.52

dismissalComment.html: knocks him over! Slightly quicker and this might have been a little shorter than the previous one. This skids through, meaning that Salt, who is trying to force it through the off side again, is a tad late on the stroke. Goes past the bat and thunders into the stumps!

images.caption: Harpreet Brar castled Phil Salt
images.longCaption: Harpreet Brar castled Phil Salt, Delhi Capitals vs Punjab Kings, IPL 2023, Delhi, May 13, 2023

dismissalText.commentary: Mitchell Marsh lbw b Chahar 3 (4b 0x4 0x6 7m) SR: 75

dismissalComment.html: huge appeal, and given! Full delivery fizzed into off stump. Marsh looks for the cute, little paddle again but this time, gets into a slightly awkward position. Does not make contact as the ball pins him on the pads. After deliberation, Marsh decides to review! The impact might be the only thing under consideration here. Nothing on UltraEdge, as expected. It is Umpire's Call on Impact and the ball is just about clipping the off stump! Marsh has to go!

images.caption: Rahul Chahar trapped Mitchell Marsh lbw
images.longCaption: Rahul Chahar trapped Mitchell Marsh lbw, Delhi Capitals vs Punjab Kings, IPL 2023, Delhi, May 13, 2023

dismissalText.long: c Sikandar Raza b Harpreet Brar
dismissalText.commentary: Rilee Rossouw c Sikandar Raza b Harpreet Brar 5 (5b 1x4 0x6 6m) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: holes out to deep mid wicket! Given a bit of air on a full length on leg stump. Rossouw advances and tries to mow it over long on. The bat face, though, closes on impact and he arrows it straight down Raza's throat at deep mid wicket!

dismissalText.commentary: Axar Patel lbw b Chahar 1 (2b 0x4 0x6 12m) SR: 50

dismissalComment.html: one brings two, two brings three! Full delivery on middle and leg stump. Axar has a swish at it but is not quite to the pitch of the ball. It goes past the bat and pins him on the front pad. Axar has reviewed this and he would hope it has spun enough to miss leg stump. No bat involved, as expected, but Ball Tracking shows that the ball would have kissed the outside of leg stump. Umpire's Call and DC are now five down!

images.caption: Rahul Chahar leaps in celebration
images.longCaption: Rahul Chahar leaps in celebration, Delhi Capitals vs Punjab Kings, IPL 2023, Delhi, May 13, 2023

images.caption: Rahul Chahar celebrates after trapping Axar Patel lbw
images.longCaption: Rahul Chahar celebrates after trapping Axar Patel lbw, Delhi Capitals vs Punjab Kings, IPL 2023, Delhi, May 13, 2023

dismissalText.commentary: Manish Pandey b Harpreet Brar 0 (3b 0x4 0x6 7m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: and he cleans Pandey up with an absolute corker! Fired into the track on a length on middle and leg stump. The ball drifts into Pandey and he thinks he can work it to leg. The ball, though, grips and spins square past his bat. Smashes into the top of off stump and DC are in all sorts of trouble now!

images.caption: Harpreet Brar bowled Manish Pandey for a duck
images.longCaption: Harpreet Brar bowled Manish Pandey for a duck, Delhi Capitals vs Punjab Kings, IPL 2023, Delhi, May 13, 2023

dismissalText.commentary: Aman Hakim Khan c Harpreet Brar b Ellis 16 (18b 1x4 1x6 24m) SR: 88.88

dismissalComment.html: Ellis gets Aman! Slower delivery dug into the track outside off stump. Aman tries to muscle it over cow corner but does not time it at all. The ball spoons up towards deep mid wicket, where Brar runs in quite a bit from the fence and takes a low catch! Is that the game?

dismissalText.commentary: Praveen Dubey b Ellis 16 (20b 2x4 0x6 29m) SR: 80

dismissalComment.html: Dubey misses, Ellis hits! Full, fast and this zones in on middle and leg stump. Dubey tries to tonk it into tomorrow but gets nowhere close to the ball. He is, in fact, beaten for pace and hears the death rattle soon after!

seriesStandings.notes:
The 2023 IPL will give its 10 teams seedings and place them in two "virtual" groups during the league phase of the tournament.

Group A - Mumbai Indians, Kolkata Knight Riders, Rajasthan Royals, Delhi Capitals and Lucknow Super Giants.
Group B - Chennai Super Kings, Sunrisers Hyderabad, Royal Challengers Bangalore, Punjab Kings and Gujarat Titans

10 teams will play a total of 14 matches - seven home and seven away. Each team will play the five teams of the other group twice and the other four from their own group once

At the conclusion of the league stage, the top 4 teams will qualify for the playoffs
